title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Generate a Wayang plan that computes, for each nation and each year, the total profit for all parts whose name contains the substring ‘green’. Profit is defined as (l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount)) - (ps_supplycost * l_quantity). Join the part, supplier, lineitem, partsupp, orders, and nation tables through their keys. Extract the order year, filter parts so that p_name contains ‘green’, and group the results by nation and year. Output in a textfile.

(SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_orderdate FROM orders) as X

(SELECT l_orderkey, l_partkey, l_suppkey, l_extendedprice, l_discount, l_quantity FROM lineitem) as X
(SELECT ps_partkey, ps_suppkey, ps_supplycost FROM partsupp) as X

(SELECT n_nationkey, n_name FROM nation) as X
